Based on my research, here is my findings:

The finance packs (both the preliminary v1 and the final restated v2, approved 15 July 2026) report the group-wide qualified pipeline at 13.510 (EUR 13.51m) for Q2 2026 actual — matching the claim. However, the Q2 2026 Quarterly Update (investor/staff brief) states "EUR 13.26 million" for the same metric. The 13.26 figure doesn't correspond to either finance-pack version (v1 already carried 13.510), so it isn't a pre-restatement value, and no document explicitly supersedes the update's figure. The regional "Qualified commercial pipeline" (13.053) is a different scope (regional/local CRM) and doesn't compete.

